@jamieinfinity I finally got around to testing this out and it looks good to me with one change:

```python
        if start_time:
            time_init = start_time
            if not isinstance(time_init, str):
                time_init = start_time.strftime('%H:%M')
            url = url + ('/time/%s' % (time_init))
```

The key is the addition of `time/` to the url. Without it, fitbit matches a [different API endpoint](https://wiki.fitbit.com/display/API/API-Browse-Activities) and returns a list of activity categories instead. A couple URLs in the tests also need to be updated because of this. Could you make the change in your branch? If you aren't going to for whatever reason, please just let me know and I'll merge this as is and make the changes on my end. Thanks again!

